We did.

365
00:13:36,124 --> 00:13:39,084
He was furious
about "Every Rose Has A --"

366
00:13:39,127 --> 00:13:41,347
about the reality show.

367
00:13:41,390 --> 00:13:44,916
And after years of the press
feeding off of his grief,

368
00:13:44,959 --> 00:13:47,832
yeah, it was believable
that he could've snapped.

369
00:13:47,875 --> 00:13:49,964
This is absurd.
You do know that?

370
00:13:50,008 --> 00:13:50,878
Alright, sir,
can you tell me where you were

371
00:13:50,922 --> 00:13:52,314
yesterday afternoon?

372
00:13:52,358 --> 00:13:54,882
I was in the office,
morning to midnight.

373
00:13:54,926 --> 00:13:56,884
Ask any one
of my employees.

374
00:13:56,928 --> 00:13:58,625
I didn't do this.

375
00:13:58,668 --> 00:14:00,627
Any idea who did?

376
00:14:00,670 --> 00:14:03,717
I can tell you that
whoever killed that man,

377
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:06,851
his last name is Thorsen.

378
00:14:06,894 --> 00:14:09,679
I blame myself for ever letting
them into Patrick's life.

379
00:14:09,723 --> 00:14:11,029
They're a sick family.

380
00:14:11,072 --> 00:14:13,466
And Aaron is not
the only killer among them.

381
