00:19:02,495 --> 00:19:05,019
But the footage -- from
"Every Rose Has A Thorsen" --

513
00:19:05,062 --> 00:19:07,587
we saw it.That was for the show.

514
00:19:07,630 --> 00:19:09,371
What, are you saying
you staged it?

515
00:19:09,415 --> 00:19:12,635
It's a reality show.
Of course we staged it.

516
00:19:12,679 --> 00:19:14,681
I can prove it.
I have the rest of the footage.

517
00:19:14,724 --> 00:19:16,900
Boy, you better get
the hell up out of here!

518
00:19:19,686 --> 00:19:21,122
What the hell was that?!

519
00:19:21,166 --> 00:19:23,472
Are you seriously doing this
to me again?!

520
00:19:23,516 --> 00:19:24,473
In my own house!

521
00:19:24,517 --> 00:19:26,823
You got some nerve!

522
00:19:26,867 --> 00:19:28,651
L-Let's talk about all the women
you slept with

523
00:19:28,695 --> 00:19:30,436
when you were F-Flex?

524
00:19:30,479 --> 00:19:32,438
Cut!

525
00:19:32,481 --> 00:19:34,440
Cut, cut, cut, cut.

526
00:19:34,483 --> 00:19:37,791
Linc, buddy,
you're going off-script.

527
00:19:37,834 --> 00:19:38,966
"I can't believe
you're seriously

528
00:19:39,009 --> 00:19:40,272
doing this to me again"?

529
00:19:40,315 --> 00:19:41,882
That's not the line.

530
00:19:41,925 --> 00:19:43,318
Yeah, man,
I was improv'ing a little.

531
00:19:43,362 --> 00:19:45,190
Yeah, maybe not do that,
okay?

532
00:19:45,233 --> 00:19:46,843
It's a lot more powerful
if this is the first time

533
00:19:46,887 --> 00:19:48,236
Yvonne has stepped out
on you.

534
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:50,238
Okay.
So, Morris, how did I do?

535
00:19:50,282 --> 00:19:51,892
It was a bit big.

536
00:19:51,935 --> 00:19:53,807
Yeah, maybe, uh,
dial it back a hair.

537
00:19:53,850 --> 00:19:55,025
Let's go again.

538
00:19:55,069 --> 00:19:56,636
Back to one.

539
00:19:56,679 --> 00:19:57,898
Go.

540
00:19:57,941 --> 00:19:58,986
We're making a show,
people.

541
00:20:00,901 --> 00:20:03,556
None of that was in the footage
you turned over to us.

542
00:20:03,599 --> 00:20:05,210
Oops. My bad.

543
00:20:05,253 --> 00:20:07,516
We want everything --
now --

544
00:20:07,560 --> 00:20:09,518
or you'll be arrested
for obstruction.

545
00:20:09,562 --> 00:20:11,999
Ooh, that was good.

546
00:20:12,042 --> 00:20:14,001
Do you think I can get
a copy of that?

547
00:20:14,044 --> 00:20:16,003
That will play really well
in the show.

548
00:20:16,046 --> 00:20:17,700
Mrs. Thorsen,
this is serious.

549
00:20:17,744 --> 00:20:19,528
Morris Mackey was murdered
in your house.

550
00:20:19,572 --> 00:20:21,095
Your son
is still a suspect.

551
00:20:21,138 --> 00:20:23,140
Just like the police
to only focus

552
00:20:23,184 --> 00:20:25,273
on what's
in front of their nose.

553
00:20:25,317 --> 00:20:27,928
Morris Mackey didn't just appear
out of thin air

554
00:20:27,971 --> 00:20:29,408
when he started working
for me.

555
00:20:29,451 --> 00:20:31,975
Honey,
the man had enemies.

556
00:20:37,198 --> 00:20:38,634
They're the crazy ones!

557
00:20:38,678 --> 00:20:40,157
We're the sane ones!

558
00:20:40,201 --> 00:20:42,290
You're the cult!
You're sheep!

559
00:20:42,334 --> 00:20:44,423
Prior to working
with the Thorsen family,

560
00:20:44,466 --> 00:20:47,948
Morris had been hired by a bunch
of QAnon conspiracy theorists.

561
00:20:47,991 --> 00:20:49,950
Apparently, they didn't like
the negative publicity

562
00:20:49,993 --> 00:20:51,212
they were getting,

563
00:20:51,256 --> 00:20:53,258
and they wanted
to show their side.

564
00:20:53,301 --> 00:20:54,476
Try to control
the narrative.

565
00:20:54,520 --> 00:20:55,738
Mm.
So what happened?

566
00:20:55,782 --> 00:20:57,697
Morris was allowed
into the inner sanctum.

567
00:20:57,740 --> 00:21:00,439
Conducted dozens of interviews
with founders and followers.

568
00:21:00,482 --> 00:21:02,484
But he didn't make
a propaganda film,

569
00:21:02,528 --> 00:21:03,790
he told the truth.

570
00:21:03,833 --> 00:21:05,052
We're in a war.

571
00:21:05,095 --> 00:21:06,793
Every one of us is prepared
to start killing

572
00:21:06,836 --> 00:21:07,968
for our freedom.

573
00:21:08,011 --> 00:21:09,143
Morris may have won
an Emmy,

574
00:21:09,186 --> 00:21:10,797
but he also pissed off
a lot of unhinged

575
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:12,538
and hyper-violent people.

576
00:21:12,581 --> 00:21:14,148
The storm is coming.

577
00:21:14,191 --> 00:21:14,801
There will be retribution.

578
00:21:17,566 --> 00:21:21,004
I've heard rumors
that you have insight into
the QAnon angle on this case.

579
00:21:21,048 --> 00:21:23,137
Have you ever tried to put
toothpaste back in the tube?

580
00:21:23,180 --> 00:21:25,226
Look, I know
it's an expression,

581
00:21:25,269 --> 00:21:27,706
but have you actually tried
to do it?

582
00:21:27,750 --> 00:21:29,273
I have.

583
00:21:29,317 --> 00:21:31,101
It's basically impossible.

584
00:21:31,145 --> 00:21:32,842
And what do you think Q
is trying to tell people

585
00:21:32,886 --> 00:21:35,584
with his Q-Drops,
these cryptic messages?

586
00:21:35,627 --> 00:21:37,151
I really wasn't trying
to say anything.

587
00:21:37,194 --> 00:21:40,110
I was just typing, and maybe
I got a little carried away.

588
00:21:40,154 --> 00:21:41,677
Wait.
What did you say?

589
00:21:43,157 --> 00:21:46,508
Well, I guess now is as good
a time as any to reveal it.

590
00:21:48,902 --> 00:21:50,599
I'm Q.

591
00:21:50,642 --> 00:21:51,948
Smitty is Q?

592
00:21:51,992 --> 00:21:52,949
I'm sorry. What?

593
00:21:52,993 --> 00:21:54,559
Lord, give me strength.
What?

594
00:21:54,603 --> 00:21:57,127
A lot of writers
use pseudonyms.

595
00:21:57,171 --> 00:21:59,826
Q is my first initial,
so...

596
00:21:59,869 --> 00:22:01,262
Hey, is my name down there?

597
00:22:03,438 --> 00:22:04,482
But it was an accident?

598
00:22:04,526 --> 00:22:06,876
He -- He didn't start it
on purpose?

599
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,008
That's what he said.

600
00:22:08,051 --> 00:22:09,487
Yeah,
sounds like Smitty.

601
00:22:09,531 --> 00:22:11,620
I was trying to start
the fan-fiction club

602
00:22:11,663 --> 00:22:14,231
for "This Is Us,"
and things just got out of hand.

603
00:22:14,275 --> 00:22:15,842
What the hell
does "This is Us" fanfic

604
00:22:15,885 --> 00:22:17,191
have to do with a cult?

605
00:22:17,234 --> 00:22:20,324
I mistakenly mixed cough syrup
with diet pills

606
00:22:20,368 --> 00:22:22,979
when I was writing
this satanic, alien story line

607
00:22:23,023 --> 00:22:25,112
for Jack and Rebecca.

608
00:22:25,155 --> 00:22:27,897
I woke up the next morning
and read it --

609
00:22:27,941 --> 00:22:29,246
none of it made sense.

610
00:22:29,290 --> 00:22:31,553
But, overnight,
I'd gotten so many followers,

611
00:22:31,596 --> 00:22:32,859
I just went with it.

612
00:22:32,902 --> 00:22:35,339
You can't put the toothpaste
back in the tube.

613
00:22:36,950 --> 00:22:40,649
Morris had received threats from
hundreds of QAnon followers,

614
00:22:40,692 --> 00:22:43,130
but when we started
investigating them,

615
00:22:43,173 --> 00:22:45,175
one immediately stood out.

616
00:22:45,219 --> 00:22:46,481
Tell me
about Connor Hart.

617
00:22:46,524 --> 00:22:47,961
What about him
got your attention?

618
00:22:48,004 --> 00:22:50,659
Well, he was working as a
cameraman on the reality show,

619
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:52,922
so -- that.

620
00:22:54,097 --> 00:22:56,621
Connor,
thanks for coming down.

621
00:22:56,665 --> 00:22:58,014
I'm not in trouble, am I?

622
00:22:58,058 --> 00:23:01,104
No. We just need to clear
a few things up.

623
00:23:01,148 --> 00:23:03,498
I told you
everything I know.

624
00:23:03,541 --> 00:23:06,631
I was getting a battery,
and he was just lying there.

625
00:23:06,675 --> 00:23:08,155
I'm not sure
if you're aware,

626
00:23:08,198 --> 00:23:10,679
but it's common to run
background checks on witnesses.

627
00:23:10,722 --> 00:23:12,420
And when we looked into you,
we discovered

628
00:23:12,463 --> 00:23:13,682
that you're a member
of QAnon.

629
00:23:13,725 --> 00:23:15,336
No, no, no, I --

630
00:23:15,379 --> 00:23:17,338
I may have gone
to a political rally or two,

631
00:23:17,381 --> 00:23:18,730
but I'm really
not into that.

632
00:23:18,774 --> 00:23:20,471
I swear.

633
00:23:20,515 --> 00:23:22,125
We're in a war.

634
00:23:22,169 --> 00:23:24,998
Every one of us is prepared to
start killing for our freedom.

635
00:23:25,041 --> 00:23:26,564
The storm is coming.

636
00:23:26,608 --> 00:23:28,001
There will be retribution.

637
00:23:33,571 --> 00:23:36,139
So, clearly,
you are a follower of Q.

638
00:23:36,183 --> 00:23:37,358
Why would you work
for Morris?

639
00:23:37,401 --> 00:23:38,968
Honestly?

640
00:23:39,012 --> 00:23:40,404
I realized
Morris was the best thing

641
00:23:40,448 --> 00:23:42,145
that could have happened
to the movement.

642
00:23:42,189 --> 00:23:43,364
That makes no sense.

643
00:23:43,407 --> 00:23:45,192
But it does.

644
00:23:45,235 --> 00:23:47,977
Morris's documentary exposed
who was a true believer.

645
00:23:48,021 --> 00:23:50,284
And who wasn't.

646
00:23:50,327 --> 00:23:52,547
He never admitted it,

647
00:23:52,590 --> 00:23:55,637
but I think Morris
was working for Q.

648
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:57,508
That's why I followed him
to the next gig.

649
00:23:57,552 --> 00:23:59,684
Do you still consider yourself
a believer of Q?

650
00:23:59,728 --> 00:24:02,818
Well, some stuff
didn't come true.

651
00:24:02,861 --> 00:24:04,951
The London bombing,
the Pope's arrest,

652
00:24:04,994 --> 00:24:06,343
Zuckerberg still has a job.

653
00:24:06,387 --> 00:24:08,084
January 20th
came and went,

654
00:24:08,128 --> 00:24:10,217
March 4th came and went.

655
00:24:10,260 --> 00:24:13,002
I'm starting to think Kennedy
is still dead.

656
00:24:13,046 --> 00:24:14,134
Both of them.

657
00:24:14,177 --> 00:24:15,439
Mm.

658
00:24:15,483 --> 00:24:18,442
So you don't believe
in Q anymore?

659
00:24:18,486 --> 00:24:20,183
Oh, I believe every word.

660
00:24:20,227 --> 00:24:21,706
Connor was, um --

661
00:24:21,750 --> 00:24:23,578
Deranged?

662
00:24:23,621 --> 00:24:26,015
Let's say...
reality-challenged,

663
00:24:26,059 --> 00:24:27,799
which doesn't make him
a killer.

664
00:24:27,843 --> 00:24:30,585
No. And the fact that he had
a camera on his shoulder

665
00:24:30,628 --> 00:24:32,456
for the entire
murder window

666
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:34,458
means that he couldn't
have killed Morris,

667
00:24:34,502 --> 00:24:36,591
so we were back
to square one.

668
00:24:36,634 --> 00:24:38,419
When the QAnon lead
didn't pan out,

669
00:24:38,462 --> 00:24:40,247
how did you pick up
the pieces of the case?

670
00:24:40,290 --> 00:24:42,989
We rolled up our sleeves
and put in the hours.

671
00:24:43,032 --> 00:24:44,512
We took on
the painstaking process

672
00:24:44,555 --> 00:24:47,254
of reviewing
every piece of video Morris shot

673
00:24:47,297 --> 00:24:48,733
in the weeks
before he died,

674
00:24:48,777 --> 00:24:52,737
including the footage
Yvonne "forgot" to give us.

675
00:24:52,781 --> 00:24:54,565
Until I found something
that changed everything.

676
00:24:54,609 --> 00:24:57,090
♪♪

677
00:24:57,133 --> 00:24:59,309
Lopez!

678
00:24:59,353 --> 00:25:00,876
Come look at this!

679
00:25:00,919 --> 00:25:02,573
So I immediately informed
Detective Lopez

680
00:25:02,617 --> 00:25:03,531
of what I discovered.

681
00:25:03,574 --> 00:25:04,314
Look what I just found.

682
00:25:04,358 --> 00:25:05,750
Wow.

683
00:25:05,794 --> 00:25:06,751
What?

684
00:25:06,795 --> 00:25:08,623
Look.

685
00:25:08,666 --> 00:25:10,320
Okay.

686
00:25:16,022 --> 00:25:18,676
I thought I knew everything
about Patrick's murder.

687
00:25:18,720 --> 00:25:20,983
I had done my homework.

688
00:25:21,027 --> 00:25:25,422
But the truth was hiding right
in front of me all this time.

689
00:25:25,466 --> 00:25:28,469
I know
who killed Patrick Hayes.

690
00:25:28,512 --> 00:25:29,644
And I can prove it. I --

691
00:25:32,603 --> 00:25:33,604
Uh, someone's here.

692
00:25:35,041 --> 00:25:36,216
More to follow.

693
00:25:36,259 --> 00:25:37,608
That video
was recorded

694
00:25:37,652 --> 00:25:39,523
minutes before
Morris was murdered.

695
00:25:42,288 --> 00:25:44,726
I mean, Morris
claiming that he knew

696
00:25:44,769 --> 00:25:45,988
who the killer was
must've been energizing for you.

697
00:25:46,031 --> 00:25:46,989
Finally. A break
in your roommate's murder --

698
00:25:47,032 --> 00:25:49,339
No, he --
He wasn't my roommate.

699
00:25:49,382 --> 00:25:51,820
And I -- I hate when people
call him that --

700
00:25:51,863 --> 00:25:53,343
you know, like we found
each other

701
00:25:53,386 --> 00:25:55,737
on some French Craigslist
or something like that.

702
00:25:55,780 --> 00:25:57,086
Patrick was my best friend,

703
00:25:57,129 --> 00:25:58,566
from the time
that we were little kids.

704
00:25:58,609 --> 00:25:59,828
I mean, I was at his house
so often,

705
00:25:59,871 --> 00:26:01,656
his dad bought us
two of everything,

706
00:26:01,699 --> 00:26:02,961
you know, like siblings.

707
00:26:03,005 --> 00:26:04,746
Yeah,
Patrick was my brother.

708
00:26:04,789 --> 00:26:06,182
How did it feel to hear
that Morris thought

709
00:26:06,225 --> 00:26:08,053
he'd discovered
who killed Patrick?

710
00:26:08,097 --> 00:26:12,405
I mean, there had been
so many theories over the years.

711
00:26:12,449 --> 00:26:15,147
And so many people think
that they had it figured out.

712
00:26:15,191 --> 00:26:18,716
I -- I just never really
got my hopes up about it.

713
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:20,500
This was different, though.
I mean, he made a break

714
00:26:20,544 --> 00:26:21,850
in the case
and died minutes later.

715
00:26:21,893 --> 00:26:23,765
You have to see
the connection.

716
00:26:23,808 --> 00:26:28,160
Well, uh, in the words
of Detective Harper --

717
00:26:28,204 --> 00:26:31,294
We look for facts,
not stories.

718
00:26:31,337 --> 00:26:32,991
Yeah, sure, but, I mean,
the timing --

719
00:26:33,035 --> 00:26:35,167
I mean, these murders
had to be related.

720
00:26:35,211 --> 00:26:37,648
Whoever killed Patrick
also killed Morris.

721
00:26:37,692 --> 00:26:38,910
Is it possible
Morris found out

722
00:26:38,954 --> 00:26:40,651
that Aaron was the killer
all along?

723
00:26:40,695 --> 00:26:42,174
Not a chance.
The Paris police

724
00:26:42,218 --> 00:26:45,700
never had a shred of evidence
against Aaron.

725
00:26:45,743 --> 00:26:47,397
They fumbled
the entire case.

726
00:26:47,440 --> 00:26:48,703
Right off the bat,
the paparazzi

727
00:26:48,746 --> 00:26:50,487
completely contaminated
the crime scene.

728
00:27:07,722 --> 00:27:09,811
But Aaron's DNA
was all over the murder weapon.

729
00:27:09,854 --> 00:27:11,421
You mean the knife
the killer pulled

730
00:27:11,464 --> 00:27:13,858
from the kitchen block
on Aaron and Patrick's counter?

731
00:27:13,902 --> 00:27:16,426
What -- What do you want to bet
that if we went to your house,

732
00:27:16,469 --> 00:27:18,602
we'd find your DNA
all over your stuff, too?

733
00:27:18,646 --> 00:27:20,909
I mean --

734
00:27:20,952 --> 00:27:22,345
Was that too mean?

735
00:27:22,388 --> 00:27:24,956
No, that actually
felt good.

736
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,523
It was a dumb question.

737
00:27:26,566 --> 00:27:28,046
From the beginning,
the French police's case

738
00:27:28,090 --> 00:27:29,700
against Aaron
seemed flawed --

739
00:27:29,744 --> 00:27:31,702
Oh, yeah.
Their case was a mess --

740
00:27:31,746 --> 00:27:34,270
and their forensics
were compromised.

741
00:27:34,313 --> 00:27:36,707
I mean, the theory
that Aaron killed Patrick

742
00:27:36,751 --> 00:27:38,970
because he didn't do his share
of the chores never made sense.

743
00:27:39,014 --> 00:27:41,059
For one thing,
they had a housekeeper.

744
00:27:41,103 --> 00:27:42,626
For another,
Aaron is not a psychopath,

745
00:27:42,670 --> 00:27:44,454
which you would have to be
to stab your roommate

746
00:27:44,497 --> 00:27:46,586
for leaving dirty dishes
in the sink.

747
00:27:46,630 --> 00:27:50,068
I mean, I've come close to
stabbing him over dirty dishes,

748
00:27:50,112 --> 00:27:52,636
but that's different --
we're married.

749
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:53,898
Mm.

750
00:27:53,942 --> 00:27:55,204
What do you say
to the theory

751
00:27:55,247 --> 00:27:57,249
that Aaron had a falling out
with his roommate?

752
00:27:57,293 --> 00:27:59,991
Aaron and Patrick
were out partying that night.

753
00:28:00,035 --> 00:28:01,689
Does that sound like
a broken friendship

754
00:28:01,732 --> 00:28:03,299
careening towards murder?

755
00:28:03,342 --> 00:28:05,518
By his own admission, Aaron was
taking prescription drugs.

756
00:28:05,562 --> 00:28:08,391
Yeah. For a football injury
he got in high school.

757
00:28:08,434 --> 00:28:11,611
They impair your ability
to operate heavy machinery,

758
00:28:11,655 --> 00:28:14,397
not -- not turn you
into a hardened killer.

759
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:15,615
♪♪

760
00:28:15,659 --> 00:28:18,009
Aaron passed out early.

761
00:28:18,053 --> 00:28:19,228
Woke up in the middle
of the night.

762
00:28:19,271 --> 00:28:22,753
Went to pee
and found Patrick's body.

763
00:28:22,797 --> 00:28:32,023
♪♪

764
00:28:32,067 --> 00:28:34,765
The French police took one look
at a young Black man,

765
00:28:34,809 --> 00:28:36,680
and decided he was the killer.

766
00:28:36,724 --> 00:28:39,161
I mean, they didn't even pursue
any other suspects.

